      <div class="row-fluid">
        <p> Kunal Mehta truly embodies the underdog story.  Born into poverty in the Slums of Shaolin, Kunal never had a shot at a formal education of any sort.  By the age of 6, Kunal had been kicked out of school and was forced to survive solely on his wits, natural charm, and dashing good looks.  He made his living hustling tourists and visitors in improvised dance-offs.  Unfortunately, at the tender age of 12, Kunal’s operation had been shut down by the local law enforcement.  Forced to find a new way to survive, Kunal’s story takes an uplifting turn; Kunal began picking up computer science by offering “safety services” to local residents who needed protection.  Kunal would perform ocular patdowns and intimidate would-be ne’er-do-wells with his muscular physique – in exchange for these services, Kunal received small bits of programming knowledge from his clients.  Ultimately, Kunal was able to pick up enough computer science know-how to infiltrate the rapidly-aging Telebears system, and enroll in classes at UC Berkeley.  Here he currently resides, protecting the weak and fragile citizens of Berkeley, coding like a boss, and sharing his story of success with others. </p>  
